According to http://arxiv.org/abs/1304.5082
Yarnoz, Sanchez, McInnes (Celestial Mechanics and Dynamical Astronomy):

diameter (m) D = 1329km * 10 ^ (-H/5) * p_v ^ (-1/2)

H = absolute magnitude
p_v = albedo, assumed to range from .05-.5 (dark-icy)

.15 default is reasonable

also helpful: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Standard_asteroid_physical_characteristics

http://www.physics.sfasu.edu/astro/asteroids/sizemagnitude.html
